CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 17, 1940, pg. 20, reads: "Here they are...Lionel Hampton, the nation's No. 1 vibraharpist and Billy Rowe, as they arrived at Pittsburgh's County Airport Friday afternoon to participate in festivities incident to selecting 'Miss Pittsburgh' in 'Miss Bronze America' contest. - Harris Foto."
TitMainTitle: Jazz musician Lionel Hampton and Pittsburgh Courier reporter Billy Rowe waving in front of TWA airplane at Allegheny County Airport, West Mifflin
